  "prompt": "Where is good apartment near Deloitte Chicago?",
  "response": "When looking for an apartment near Deloitte's Chicago office, which is located at 111 South Wacker Drive in the Loop, you'll want to consider neighborhoods that are close to this area for convenience. Here are some good options:\n\n1. **The Loop**:\n   - **Pros**: Closest to the Deloitte office, vibrant with lots of amenities.\n   - **Cons**: Can be pricier and more bustling.\n   - **Example**: The Shoreham at Lakeshore East (400 E. South Water St.) offers luxury apartments with great views and amenities.\n\n2. **South Loop**:\n   - **Pros**: Close to the Loop but slightly less expensive, with a more relaxed atmosphere.\n   - **Cons**: Slightly farther from the Deloitte office.\n   - **Example**: The Flats (801 S. Financial Pl.) offers modern apartments with a fitness center and rooftop deck.\n\n3. **West Loop**:\n   - **Pros**: Trendy area with great dining and nightlife options, still very close to the Loop.\n   - **Cons**: Can be on the pricier side.\n   - **Example**: The Parker Fulton Market (651 W. Fulton St.) offers stylish apartments in a vibrant neighborhood.\n\n4. **River North**:\n   - **Pros**: Known for its art galleries, restaurants, and nightlife, with easy access to the Loop.\n   - **Cons**: Can be quite busy and expensive.\n   - **Example**: The Montgomery (500 W. Superior St.) offers upscale living with great amenities.\n\n5. **Streeterville**:\n   - **Pros**: Close to the lakefront, with easy access to the Loop and great amenities.\n   - **Cons**: Can be pricier.\n   - **Example**: The Olympia Centre (161 E. Chicago Ave.) offers luxury high-rise living with stunning views.\n\nWhen choosing an apartment, consider factors like commute time, budget, and lifestyle preferences. Websites like Zillow, Apartments.com, and StreetEasy can help you browse available listings in these neighborhoods.",
